physical_examinations.relevant_findings: Patient A-1: BMI 20.4, bilateral aural fullness worse in left ear, Tullio phenomenon and Hennebert sign present only in left ear. Patient A-2: BMI 28.1, Hennebert sign present in right ear only. Patient A-3: BMI 26.9, mild sensorineural loss at 2 kHz bilaterally.
physical_examinations.changes_over_time: Patient A-1 had resolution of dizziness and left ear symptoms after surgery. Patient A-2 declined surgery; no notable change described for A-3.

physical_examinations.relevant_findings: Patient B-1: BMI 16.9, bilateral sensorineural hearing loss, normal otomicroscopy, CT showed dehiscence over left superior semicircular canal. Patient B-2: BMI 27.2, normal otomicroscopy, bilateral dehiscence at the arcuate eminence.

Patient C-1: BMI 39.1, normal otomicroscopy, CT revealed dehiscence of bone over left superior semicircular canal. Patient C-2: BMI 30.3, normal otomicroscopy, small dehiscence over right superior semicircular canal.
